## Chakra UI Rules

### Theme & Design System

- Centralize theme in `theme/`; extend Chakra theme with tokens (colors, space, radii, typography).
- Define components theme overrides in `theme/components/`.
- Use design tokens; avoid hardcoded values in components.

### Components & Styling

- Prefer Chakra components over raw HTML.
- Use style props for simple cases; use `sx` or `styled` for complex variants.
- Create reusable components for common patterns (buttons, form fields, modals).

### Responsiveness

- Use responsive style props (array/object syntax) for breakpoints.
- Use `Stack`, `Grid`, and `Flex` for layout.

### Accessibility

- Use Chakra form components with labels and helper text.
- Ensure contrast ratios meet WCAG AA.

### Theming Practices

- Use `variant`, `size`, and `colorScheme` instead of inline styles.
- Avoid overriding Chakra CSS with `!important`.

